The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Gambhir pulled up
                                                                                                                       7                                      Gambhir pulled up
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Gautam Gambhir, the Delhi DareDevils captain, was Friday reprimanded for breaching the Indian Premier League code of conduct after Wednesdays match versus the Rajasthan Royals at the Kotla,         
	Gambhir was reported by IPL supremo Lalit Modi and the India opener admitted to the charge after receiving details of the report.         
	The offence relates to comments made by Gambhir at the post-match presentation following the thumping victory by 67 runs over the Jaipur franchise.         
	Gambhir pleaded guilty to a level 1 offence (section 2.1.7), which relates to Public criticism of, or inappropriate comment in relation to an incident occurring in a match, any player, team official, match official or team participating in any match, irrespective of when such criticism or comment is made.                                                                                                                     
